<br>
Generally, in action games you are FORCED to choose one direction, there is hardly any plot other than the main storyline and you kill lots of things all which lead up to the finally, THE MAIN BOSS FIGHT. In RPGs, you more so than not get choices on where to go next and your reactions to situations and quests, though they generally all lead up to a main fight but is not limited to that.<br>
<br>
Everquest gives you choices right as you step out into Norrath. You can go kill a bat or start your newbie quests. Do you have to kill a bat? No. Do you have to do your newbie quests? No. Will it hurt you in the long run if you don't kill that bat? Probably not. Will it hurt you in the long run if you don't do your newbie quests? Probably not. Everquest is actually, pretty revolutionary. How many games are there that you can choose how you end the game or even start it? Not many. Everquest is plot based but its not limited to that, you have the choice to go out and do what you want. By all means, you don't even have to level, you can do tradeskills or just talk with people ( you know, play the commoner ).<br>
<br>
Most people that play do it because they like to play RPGs. Does that mean they have to RP? No. Well what do you consider RP? Someone playing a character that is not themself. That can be inturpreted a few different ways. Though its generally applied to Fantasy, its not limited to that.. ( think whips/chains/nurse outfits). <br>
<br>
I am certainly not dyshira but I take on dyshira's actions ingame. I heal, rez and attack things like a paladin. Do I talk in d00d speak? No, not really. I talk normally and I address everyone as their character names. There are different types of fantasy, I'm not about to start talking with harks, forsooths and myladies just to please the RP community. Go read Eddings' The Belgeriad. Any actions that Dyshira takes I could easily justify in RP, its that I choose not to do that ( example: grouping with dark elves ).<br>
<br>
As far as RP for others... Not everyone on the non RP side of the server are loot whores. The majority just like the versatility of the game and want to play on a server where they can experience that. Yeah, people sell things way over what they should be sold for, they talk in d00d, and they scratch their ass... But they did buy the game and did pay to play on a server, by all means let them do as they please ( as long as it doesn't insult others and not RPing shouldn't insult you, as it is an option and people waver that ).<br>
<br>
And to RPers - Accept the fact that people don't and will not RP. You can't make them, period but you can RP to them in hopes that something good will come out of it but don't force it on them~! If they seem to get annoyed, don't keep going, it will seriously make them hate you and just because people don't RP, doesn't mean they suck and you are superior to them, because you are not.. We are all equal and I'm not going to say otherwise.<br>
<br>
To NonRPers - Let them do what they enjoy and they'll let you do what you enjoy, mmk?<br>
<br>
K thx la~!<br>
Dyshira Bladeshine<br>
60th Crusader<br>
